commands.command: $'\n    print -Pu2 "%F{yellow}[oh-my-zsh] \'%F{red}current_branch%F{yellow}\' is deprecated, using \'%F{green}git_current_branch%F{yellow}\' instead.%f"\n    git_current_branch'
examples: $'\n    print -Pu2 "%F{yellow}[oh-my-zsh] \'%F{red}current_branch%F{yellow}\' is deprecated, using \'%F{green}git_current_branch%F{yellow}\' instead.%f"\n    git_current_branch'

commands.command: LANG=C git branch --no-color -vv | grep ": gone\]" | cut -c 3- | awk '\''{print $1}'\'' | xargs git branch -D
examples: LANG=C git branch --no-color -vv | grep ": gone\]" | cut -c 3- | awk '\''{print $1}'\'' | xargs git branch -D

commands.command: LANG=C git branch --no-color -vv | grep ": gone\]" | cut -c 3- | awk '\''{print $1}'\'' | xargs git branch -d
examples: LANG=C git branch --no-color -vv | grep ": gone\]" | cut -c 3- | awk '\''{print $1}'\'' | xargs git branch -d

commands.command: git svn dcommit && git push github $(git_main_branch):svntrunk
examples: git svn dcommit && git push github $(git_main_branch):svntrunk

commands.command: git push origin --all && git push origin --tags
examples: git push origin --all && git push origin --tags

commands.command: git rev-list --max-count=1 --format="%s" HEAD | grep -q "\--wip--" && git reset HEAD~1
examples: git rev-list --max-count=1 --format="%s" HEAD | grep -q "\--wip--" && git reset HEAD~1

commands.command: git add -A; git rm $(git ls-files --deleted) 2> /dev/null; git commit --no-verify --no-gpg-sign --message "--wip-- [skip ci]"
examples: git add -A; git rm $(git ls-files --deleted) 2> /dev/null; git commit --no-verify --no-gpg-sign --message "--wip-- [skip ci]"
